{"id":392,"date":"2017-12-03T07:00:54","date_gmt":"2017-12-03T07:00:54","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/?page_id=392"},"modified":"2017-12-03T22:53:29","modified_gmt":"2017-12-03T22:53:29","slug":"data-analytics","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/data-analytics\/","title":{"rendered":"Data analytics"},"content":{"rendered":"<h4>CASE &#8211; which customers are likely to churn?<\/h4>\n<p>The ability to predict when a customer is at a high risk of churning is valuable for every business with returning customers. Churn is defined as the\u00a0number of\u00a0customers cancelling within a time period divided by\u00a0the\u00a0number of active customers at the start of that period. In order to apply a modeling technique to predict churn, we need\u00a0to understand the customer behavior and characteristics which signal the risk of customers churn.<\/p>\n<p>In this example, I will look into an electricity company. An electricity company is a good example because customers &#8216;return&#8217; every month.<\/p>\n<h4>What characteristics are specific to churned customers?<\/h4>\n<p>First step of the churn analysis is to select the characteristics of customers which could predict churn. Characteristics can be categorized, for example:<\/p>\n<p>Customer characteristics<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Age of a person<\/li>\n<li>Number of people in household<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Behavioral characteristics<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Average amount of electricity spend per month<\/li>\n<li>Time since sign up<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Usually, you have as many characteristics as possible (for example 50) of which you can select the ones with highest prediction power.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/Correlation-plot-characteristics.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-399\" src=\"http:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/Correlation-plot-characteristics.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"354\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/Correlation-plot-characteristics.png 609w, https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/Correlation-plot-characteristics-300x212.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h4>What is the customer lifetime value for each customer?<\/h4>\n<p>Another calculation which supports the churn prediction is to calculate the customer lifetime value (CLV or LTV).\u00a0The CLV is a prediction of the total value generated by a customer in the past and in the future.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/CLV-and-lifetime.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-480\" src=\"http:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/CLV-and-lifetime-300x101.png\" alt=\"Data analytics case - CLV and lifetime\" width=\"600\" height=\"202\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/CLV-and-lifetime-300x101.png 300w, https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/CLV-and-lifetime-768x259.png 768w, https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/CLV-and-lifetime-1024x345.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/CLV-and-lifetime.png 1250w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h4>How can we predict if a customer is likely to churn?<\/h4>\n<p>A statistical model calculates the churn probability for each customer. This model uses selected characteristics, the CLV and expected lifetime. Each element is weighted such that the accuracy of churning is maximized. After developing the model, the model is applied to all customers such that we obtain the likelihood of churning for each customer. Ranking the results gives you the top X customers who are about to churn.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/Prediction-model.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-405\" src=\"http:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/Prediction-model-1024x462.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/Prediction-model-1024x462.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/Prediction-model-300x135.png 300w, https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/Prediction-model-768x346.png 768w, https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/12\/Prediction-model.png 1058w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Do you want to know more about data analytics?\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/#contact-form\">Please get in touch with me here.<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>CASE &#8211; which customers are likely to churn? The ability to predict when a customer is at a high risk of churning is valuable for every business with returning customers. Churn is defined as the\u00a0number of\u00a0customers cancelling within a time period divided by\u00a0the\u00a0number of active customers at the start of that period. In order to [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"custom-page-analyse-op-maat.php","meta":{"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/392"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.claudiatenhoope.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"